definition.value: An apo carotenoid sesquiterpenoid that consists of a cylohexene ring substituted by methyl groups at positions 2, 6 and 6 and a (1E)-1-(formyloxy)-2-methylbut-1-en-4-yl group at position 2.
A glycerol monophosphate having the phosphate group at the 2-position.
A triply-charged monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy and phospho groups of 3-phosphonopyruvic acid.
